02/02/84  chcpass

Syntax:  chcpass Person_id


Function: allows the accounting administrator to change the user's
card input password in the PNT found in >sc1.  Thus, even if the user
has changed his password with the -cpw control argument on the
++PASSWORD card, the chcpass command overrides the user's change.

A card input password consists of from one through eight ASCII
printing characters, including backspace, but excluding space and
semicolon.


Arguments:
Person_id
   is the Person_id of the user whose card input password is to be
   changed.
